Since the parabola passes through $(-1,7)$ and $(5,7),$ its equation can be written in the form
\[y = a(x + 1)(x - 5).\]Substituting $(6,10),$ we get
\[10 = a(6 + 1)(6 - 5),\]so $a = 2.$  This means the equation of the parabola is $y = 2(x + 1)(x - 5) = 2(x^2 - 4x - 5).$

We can expand $y = 2(x^2 - 4x - 5)$ to get $y = 2x^2 - 8x - 10.$  Completing the square:
\begin{align*}
y &= 2(x^2 - 4x - 5) \\
&= 2(x^2 - 4x + 4 - 4 - 5) \\
&= 2((x - 2)^2 - 9) \\
&= 2(x - 2)^2 - 18.
\end{align*}Thus, the $x$-coordinate of the vertex is $\boxed{2}.$
